elilong (UEFI Boot Manager)

elilong is a simple, lightweight UEFI bootloader for Linux,
specifically designed to handle Slackware and other distributions
with a focus on simplicity and transparency.

After installing the package, you must run the setup script as root
to deploy the bootloader to your EFI System Partition, eg:

# /usr/sbin/elilongsetup
note: only tested on x86_64 but should support 32bit and other arch's
